    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-04-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-04-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="194"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d194">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-04-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 25, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose herewith copy of communication<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d194fn1">See Senate Ex. Doc. No. 67, Fifty-third Congress,
                        third session, page 110.</note> addressed by Secreretary Herbert to the
                    British ambassador at this capital on the 19th instant, giving a complete list
                    of the officers who will have charge of our cruisers in Bering Sea and the North
                    Pacific Ocean during the present season.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
